<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <title>Weather App Help Page</title>
</head>

<body>

    {{>nav}}
    <div class="container-fluid">
        <div class="text-center py-4">
            <h2>Welcome to the Weather App</h2>
            <p class="lead">How to Use the App</p>
        </div>

        <div class="row justify-content-center align-items-center">
            <div class="col-6">
                <h4>Get Weather Information</h4>
                <p>To get weather information for a specific location, enter the location in the input field and click the "Search" button.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row justify-content-center align-items-center mt-4">
            <div class="col-6">
                <h4>View Results</h4>
                <p>Once you've searched for a location, the app will display the location's name and the current weather forecast below the search form.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row justify-content-center align-items-center mt-4">
            <div class="col-6">
                <h4>Example Usage</h4>
                <p>For example, if you want to know the weather in New York City, type "New York City" in the input field and click the "Search" button. The app will then display the weather information for New York City.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row justify-content-center align-items-center mt-4">
            <div class="col-6">
                <h4>Additional Help</h4>
                <p>If you encounter any issues or have any questions, please refer to the documentation or contact our support team for assistance.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
    <script src="/js/app.js"></script>
</body>

</html>
